              <title ref="" type="supplied">The correspondence of <persName ref="" xml:lang="en" type="supplied">Sergius Grammaticus</persName> and <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/51" xml:lang="en" type="uniform">Severus of Antioch</persName>, regarding the doctrine of the Two Natures in Christ</title>
              <note>The writings of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/430">Cyril of Alexandria</persName> are quoted on almost every page of these letters. The other authorities cited are: <persName ref="">Amphilochius</persName>, <title ref="">epist. to <persName ref="">Seleucus</persName></title>, <locus from="44b">fol. 44 b</locus>; <persName ref="">Andrew of Samosata</persName>, <locus from="28a">fol. 28 a</locus>; <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/342">Aristotle</persName>, foll. <locus from="36b">36 b</locus>, <locus from="44a">44 a</locus>; <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/354">Athanasius</persName>, foll. <locus from="21a">21 a</locus>, <locus from="26a">26 a</locus>, <locus from="43a">43 a</locus>; <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/845">Basil</persName>; <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/573">Chrysostom</persName>; <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/451">Diodorus of Tarsus</persName>, <locus from="17b">fol. 17 b</locus>; <persName ref="">Dioscorus of Alexandria</persName>, <title ref="">epist. to <persName ref="">Domnus of Antioch</persName></title>, <locus from="32a">fol. 32 a</locus>; <persName ref="">Eustathius of Antioch</persName>, <title ref="">Commentary on <abbr>Ps.</abbr><expan>Psalm</expan> xcii.</title>, <locus from="42b">fol. 42 b</locus>; <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/511">Gregory Nazianzen</persName>; <persName ref="">Julius of Rome</persName>, foll. <locus from="7b">7 b</locus>, <locus from="27b">27 b</locus>; <persName ref="">Leo of Rome</persName>, <locus from="49b">fol. 49 b</locus>; <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/655">Nestorius</persName>, foll. <locus from="24b">24 b</locus>, <locus from="49b">49 b</locus>; <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/781">Theodoret</persName>, <locus from="49b">fol. 49 b</locus>; and <title ref="">the Acts of the Council of Chalcedon</title>, <locus from="50a">fol. 50 a</locus>.
</note>
